President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring November 20, 2016, as National Child's Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of providing every child in America with the opportunity to learn, grow, and thrive in a safe and healthy environment. The Obama Administration has implemented various initiatives and policies aimed at supporting children, including efforts to combat childhood obesity, improve early childhood education, expand access to healthcare for children, and create cleaner and safer environments. The proclamation also highlights the significance of investing in education and ensuring that all children are cared for and protected from harm. It calls upon citizens to observe National Child's Day with appropriate activities and programs that promote the well-being and future success of children.